race.comment: SHOOTER MCGAVIN (3) did very well from the back to fill a minor placing when resuming at Ararat, but raced below expectations last time as favourite over 1400m at Terang, drawn the 14 gate. Has the rail here and is capable of using it. Finds a nice race and can atone. GRANDE TERRE (1) was allowed to drift back from an outside draw but found the line strongly beaten 1.4 lengths over 1000m at Terang. Fitter again and the longer sprint will suit. VERBOSITY (4) made good improvement at Horsham a week-and-a-half ago and has more to give. He is also well placed to feature. WHERE'S POPPY (5) spiked his figures beaten a whisker at Donald and that stacks up. He'll be close up holding that form.
